('NEWS0000381', '2026-01-22 03:27:19.757', 'Bloomberg', 'Robert Brown', 'Federal Reserve Signals Potential Rate Cut', 'The Federal Reserve indicated today that it may consider cutting interest rates in the coming months if inflation continues to moderate. In prepared remarks, Fed Chair emphasized that the central bank remains data-dependent but acknowledged recent progress on price stability. Treasury yields fell sharply on the news, with the 10-year note dropping 15 basis points. Equity markets rallied broadly as investors priced in a more accommodative monetary policy stance.', 'Fed signals potential rate cuts; Treasury yields fall sharply', 'https://financial-news.example.com/article/381', 'BTC,ETH', 'Crypto', 'ECONOMIC_DATA', '0.8100', 'POSITIVE', '0.8100', '2026-02-17 14:27:19.757'),
('NEWS0000382', '2026-01-22 01:47:19.757', 'Wall Street Journal', 'Lisa Garcia', 'Oil Prices Surge Amid Middle East Tensions', 'Crude oil prices jumped more than 4% today amid escalating geopolitical tensions in the Middle East. Brent crude futures rose to $95 per barrel, the highest level in six months, as traders assessed potential supply disruptions. Energy stocks outperformed the broader market, with major oil producers seeing gains of 5-8%. Analysts cautioned that sustained higher oil prices could weigh on consumer spending and corporate margins in the coming quarters.', 'Oil prices surge 4% on Middle East tensions; energy stocks outperform', 'https://financial-news.example.com/article/382', 'CAT,DE,HON,MMM', 'Industrials', 'FEATURE', '0.3200', 'NEUTRAL', '0.8200', '2026-02-17 14:27:19.757'),
